Class Another_POS

  • java.lang.Object
    • Another_POS
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Another_POS
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class includes the different methods which the main method will call on to conduct different transactions. An object of this type will be stored to a text file and restored once user opens the program again.
    See Also:

    • Method Detail

      • add_Item

        public void add_Item(java.lang.String item)
        This allows users to choose between adding a new product to stocks[] or add quantity to already existing stocks. For the first addition of stocks, the method will automatically add a product instead of quantity.

        During the addition of new stocks, the user will be required to input the different characteristics of the item. These characteristics will then be set as the attributes of the object product.

        Parameters:
        item - name of item to be added

      • Another_POS

        public void Another_POS()
        Class constructor. Initializes all attributes to null, zero or empty.

      • checkout

        public void checkout()
        This method considers items found in cart[] to be sold and is added to a linked list of sold items. Moreover, this will also calculate the total sales from the items bought through traversing the cart[]. Before moving to the next item in the cart, the element at the current index will be cleared or set to null.

        This will print the final total of all items bought.

      • delete_Item

        public void delete_Item(java.lang.String item)
        This deletes an item in stocks[]. The method will traverse the array while using a method getMod() which returns the name of the object in an index. The method will then match the names of the product the user wishes to delete and prints all matches. Finally, the user will have to select which of the items listed the user would want to delete.

        If no items are found to match the name of the user-defined item, then the program will display an error message.

        Parameters:
        item - item to delete

      • Inventory

        public void Inventory()
        This method prints the contents or attributes of stocks[] as the inventory of the system.

      • print_Cart

        public void print_Cart()
        This method prints the attributes of the content of cart[].

      • print_Search_Result

        public void print_Search_Result(boolean result)
        This method print the final result of the Search() - whether a match of the item or code being search is found.
        Parameters:
        result - determines whether there was match found

      • Sales_Report

        public void Sales_Report()
        This prints the list of sold items and total sales by calling print_List().

      • Sales

        public void Sales(java.lang.String item)
        This method replicate sales transactions. The method will accept a String item which will be used to search stocks[] with items matching the String. Matches will be printed and user has to choose which item will be part of the purchase. This item will then be added to cart[].

        The method will ask the user whether he/she would like to add more items in his/her cart. If they do, the program will recurse with a new user-defined product name. Otherwise, the program will call method checkout().

        Parameters:
        item - item to be bought

      • Search

        public boolean Search(int code)
        This method searches stocks[] with a user-defined code. It does so by the use of getCde() which returns the code of the Product object at a certain index. It will then match the int item to the result of getCde(). It will then display is a match is found.

        NOTE: ONLY ONE MATCH SHOULD BE POSSIBLE

        Parameters:
        code - code to be searched
        Returns:
        boolean returns whether a match is found or not

      • Search

        public boolean Search(java.lang.String item)
        This method searches stocks[] with a user-defined item. It does so by the use of getMod() which returns the name/model of the Product object at a certain index. It will then match the String item to the result of getMod(). All matches found will be printed.
        Parameters:
        item - item to be searched
        Returns:
        boolean returns whether a match is found or not

      • send_To_List

        private void send_To_List(Product[] sold)
        This method adds each item in cart[] to a linked list.
        Parameters:
        sold[] - equivalent to cart[]; items in this array will be added to the list.
